The paper deals with the design of neural network architectures, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). The use of a memetic algorithm for architecture design involves both optimization and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of skip connections, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the ability of the evolved network architectures to model data, which is relevant to the subfield of systems and control (cs.SY).
